The method `hp()` redefines the variable `hp` to be equal to 12 every time it is called. Try to define `hp` at a higher context, such as a global or member variable.
Try something like this:

    hp = 12;
    public static int hp() {
            return hp;
    }
        
    public void damaging() {
            hp -= Combat.damage();
    }

This way your `hp` variable is defined only once at code start or at class declaration.

